00:27:13,595 --> 00:27:18,095
高笑いする都会の喧騒 ウケ狙いならば振り向けれんぞ
The roaring din of the city, we won't look back for cheap laughs

335
00:27:18,095 --> 00:27:23,095
何連呼？忘れろ？夢流した便所見下ろしてきやがる摩天楼
How many calls? Forget it? The skyscrapers looking down on the toilet where dreams were flushed

336
00:27:23,095 --> 00:27:27,895
Oh まるで勝新みたく破天荒 伝説へとアテンド
Daring like Shintaro Katsu, attending to the legend

337
00:27:27,895 --> 00:27:30,095
怖にゃあ怖にゃあてその程度
If you're scared, it's only to that extent

338
00:27:30,095 --> 00:27:32,495
捨てろ負け惜しみ 過去の栄光
Throw away your sour grapes and past glory

339
00:27:32,495 --> 00:27:36,595
永遠なんぞはねぇて いつか天へ召され ペンで
There's no such thing as eternity, we'll be summoned to heaven someday

340
00:27:36,595 --> 00:27:41,595
書き殴ったこの魂は2PACみたく誰かの心を通過
This soul scribbled down will pass through someone's heart like 2Pac

341
00:27:41,595 --> 00:27:46,095
なぁ何か忘れちゃねぇか 人生まるで映画 皆がエンターテイナー
Hey, didn't you forget something? Life is like a movie, everyone is an entertainer

342
00:27:46,095 --> 00:27:51,095
思い出せ思想は現実化する 誰がHighway飛ばすBentayga
Remember, thoughts become reality, who's speeding down the highway in a Bentayga?

343
00:27:51,095 --> 00:27:55,595
胸の奥底 初期衝動
Deep in our chest, the primal urge

344
00:27:55,595 --> 00:28:00,095
見て見ぬフリ No, No
Turning a blind eye, no, no

345
00:28:00,095 --> 00:28:05,095
夢追い笑われ 傷だらけでギラつく My way
Chasing dreams, being laughed at, glittering on my way full of scars

346
00:28:05,095 --> 00:28:09,895
Go on! You should know who we are Forever Young

347
00:28:09,895 --> 00:28:14,895
Hey! 俺達は今日だって 若気の至りのような夢を追いかけて来た
Hey! Even today we've been chasing dreams like the rashness of youth

348
00:28:14,895 --> 00:28:19,595
Forever Young

349
00:28:19,595 --> 00:28:24,095
Hey! 変わるはずなんてない さぁ至ってやろうぜ!
Hey! There's no way it'll change, so let's reach for it!

350
00:28:24,095 --> 00:28:28,595
今日は残された人生で一番若い日だろ
Today is the youngest day of the rest of your life

351
00:28:28,595 --> 00:28:33,295
半端な覚悟ならドブに捨てな (永遠)
If your determination is half-hearted, throw it in the ditch (Eternity)

352
00:28:33,295 --> 00:28:37,095
往生際が悪いテメー笑い飛ばし誇れBetter days
Laugh off your bad sportsmanship and take pride in better days

353
00:28:37,095 --> 00:28:41,895
まだ終わらない 終わらせやしない 燃え尽きるまで (永遠)
It's not over yet, we won't let it end, until we burn out (Eternity)

354
00:28:41,895 --> 00:28:48,895
まだ終わらない 終わらせやしない くたばるまで (永遠)
It's not over yet, we won't let it end, until we drop dead (Eternity)

355
00:28:48,895 --> 00:28:53,095
Forever Young もう夢を追いかけ 本気になった心は
Forever Young, the heart that has chased dreams and got serious

356
00:28:53,095 --> 00:28:59,095
自分の指図も受けない
won't even take orders from itself

357
00:28:59,095 --> 00:29:04,095
Forever Young Hey! その思いから逃れられないなら
Forever Young, hey! If you can't escape that feeling,

358
00:29:04,095 --> 00:29:08,895
自ら向かうだけ
just head toward it yourself

359
00:29:08,895 --> 00:29:13,095
終わらせやしない 燃え尽きるまで (永遠)
We won't let it end, until we burn out (Eternity)

360
00:29:13,095 --> 00:29:17,595
まだ終わらない 終わらせやしない くたばるまで (永遠)
It's not over yet, we won't let it end, until we drop dead (Eternity)

361
00:29:17,595 --> 00:29:22,095
まだ終わらない まだ終わらない Forever Young (Forever Young)
It's not over yet, it's not over yet, Forever Young (Forever Young)

362
00:29:22,095 --> 00:29:30,095
そう 今日という日は お前に残された人生の一番若い日
That's right, today is the youngest day of the rest of your life

363
00:29:35,095 --> 00:29:37,095
イェーイ！
Yay!

364
00:29:37,095 --> 00:29:40,095
マリン、来てくれてありがとう！
Marine, thank you for coming!

365
00:29:40,095 --> 00:29:43,095
呼んでくれてありがとう！イェーイ！
Thank you for inviting me! Yay!

366
00:29:43,095 --> 00:29:49,095
いや、マジこのForever Youngって曲をマリンと一緒に歌いたかったの、Forever Youngって曲をね。
No, seriously, I really wanted to sing this song 'Forever Young' with Marine.

367
00:29:49,095 --> 00:29:52,095
あー、それはマリンがおばさんにならないように？
Ah, so that Marine won't become an old lady?

368
00:29:52,095 --> 00:29:55,095
そう、もうForeverのYoungだって言うのを、言ってやるっていうね！
Yeah, to tell you that you're Forever Young!

369
00:29:55,095 --> 00:29:57,095
そうだね、永遠にね。ヤング、うちらは。
That's right, eternally. We are young.

370
00:29:57,095 --> 00:30:00,095
みんな、みんな、Forever Young。
Everyone, everyone, Forever Young.

371
00:30:00,070 --> 00:30:01,370
悩んだ？
Were you worried?

372
00:30:01,370 --> 00:30:01,870
うーん
Yeah.

373
00:30:01,870 --> 00:30:03,470
でもマリン今日はね、今日はね
But Marine is, you see, today...

374
00:30:03,470 --> 00:30:03,870
え？
Huh?

375
00:30:03,870 --> 00:30:05,170
え、後ろ見て！
Look behind you!

376
00:30:05,170 --> 00:30:07,170
演奏してくれてる！
They're playing for us!

377
00:30:07,170 --> 00:30:08,470
気まずいよ。
This is awkward.

378
00:30:08,470 --> 00:30:10,370
今日はね、演奏してくれてるの、みんなが。
Today, everyone is playing for us!

379
00:30:10,370 --> 00:30:11,870
乗ってる、乗ってる。乗ってるよ。
They're grooving, they're grooving!

380
00:30:11,870 --> 00:30:14,070
乗ってるでしょ？え、ど、どの子と写真撮りたい？
Right? So, which one do you want to take a photo with?

381
00:30:14,070 --> 00:30:16,470
え、そんな、え、1人だけみたいな、そんななんか...
Huh? To choose just one, that's kind of...

382
00:30:16,470 --> 00:30:18,070
いや、2人選んでいい、2人選んでいい。
No, you can choose two, you can choose two!

383
00:30:18,070 --> 00:30:19,870
かわいそうじゃん、選ばれなかったの。
It'd be sad for the ones who weren't chosen.

384
00:30:19,870 --> 00:30:21,070
2人選ぼう、2人選ぼう。
Let's choose two, let's choose two.

385
00:30:21,070 --> 00:30:23,070
俺もう、コロネすきが、なんか、3...
For me, the Koronesuki are like, 3...

386
00:30:23,070 --> 00:30:25,070
いいよ、じゃあマリンが選ぶね。
Okay, then Marine will choose.

387
00:30:25,070 --> 00:30:26,370
あ、マリンが、え、え、選んで。
Oh, Marine, please choose.

388
00:30:26,370 --> 00:30:27,870
そうそう。じゃ、最初は...
Right. Well, first...

389
00:30:27,870 --> 00:30:28,870
あ、ちょっと待って。
Ah, wait a second.

390
00:30:28,870 --> 00:30:29,870
最初は...
First is...

391
00:30:29,870 --> 00:30:31,570
待って、写して、後ろ。
Wait, show the background.

392
00:30:31,570 --> 00:30:33,470
みんな下向いて。
Everyone, look down!

393
00:30:38,270 --> 00:30:39,870
細犬さん？
Hosoinu-san?

394
00:30:42,070 --> 00:30:44,270
かわいい、かわいい、かわいい。
Cute, cute, cute!

395
00:30:44,270 --> 00:30:46,070
じゃ、まず細犬と写真撮ろっか。
Well, let's take a photo with Hosoinu first.

396
00:30:46,070 --> 00:30:47,870
かわいいよ、細犬。
You're cute, Hosoinu.

397
00:30:47,870 --> 00:30:49,070
こっちおいで、マリン、こっち、こっちね。
Come over here. Marine is here, here.

398
00:30:49,070 --> 00:30:51,370
はい、細犬です。
Here is Hosoinu.

399
00:30:51,370 --> 00:30:53,670
えーと、細犬はギターかな？
Uh, is Hosoinu on guitar?

400
00:30:53,670 --> 00:30:55,670
ギターですか？細犬ちゃん。
Is it the guitar, Hosoinu-chan?

401
00:30:55,670 --> 00:30:57,070
ベロの色が...
The color of the tongue...

402
00:30:57,070 --> 00:30:58,270
乾いてる？ベロ。
Is the tongue dry?

403
00:30:58,270 --> 00:31:00,270
ベロ乾いて、ちょっと吸い込んでるんだけど、ベロの...
The tongue is dry, it's a bit sucked in, but...

404
00:31:00,270 --> 00:31:01,370
これ乾いてる。
This is dry.

405
00:31:01,370 --> 00:31:03,070
うん、乾いてる。触らないでね。
Yeah, it's dry. Don't touch it.

406
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:05,570
ごめんね、いっぱい触って。
Sorry for touching you so much.

407
00:31:05,570 --> 00:31:06,870
え、次、誰がいい？
Who do you want next?

408
00:31:06,870 --> 00:31:07,870
かわいい。あと1人、あと1人。
Cute! One more, one more.

409
00:31:07,870 --> 00:31:09,070
じゃあ、太犬？
Then, Futoinu?

410
00:31:09,070 --> 00:31:10,570
太犬ね。
Futoinu, then.

411
00:31:10,570 --> 00:31:14,270
はい、太犬はドラムです。かわいい！
Okay, Futoinu is on drums. Cute!

412
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:15,270
でかい！
Huge!

413
00:31:15,270 --> 00:31:17,070
ドゥンドゥンドゥンドゥン。
Boom, boom, boom, boom!

414
00:31:17,070 --> 00:31:18,570
かわいいね。
It's cute.

415
00:31:18,570 --> 00:31:21,070
あ、ベロの色がちょっと明るい。
Ah, the color of the tongue is a bit bright.

416
00:31:21,070 --> 00:31:24,070
細犬より。
More than Hosoinu's.

417
00:31:24,070 --> 00:31:25,570
撮った？みんな、撮った？
Did you take it? Did everyone take it?

418
00:31:25,570 --> 00:31:26,570
イェーイ、撮った？
Yay, did you take it?

419
00:31:26,570 --> 00:31:28,070
かわいい！
Cute!

420
00:31:28,070 --> 00:31:29,070
オッケーだね。
We're good.

421
00:31:29,070 --> 00:31:30,070
うん、オッケー。
Yeah, we're good.

422
00:31:30,070 --> 00:31:32,070
え、じゃ、最後さ、2人でも撮ろうよ、2人でも。
Let's take a photo of just the two of us at the end.

423
00:31:32,070 --> 00:31:34,070
あ、そうだね、2人でも撮ろう、2人でも。
Ah, right, let's take one together.

424
00:31:34,070 --> 00:31:35,570
2人で撮って。
Take a photo of the two of us.

425
00:31:38,270 --> 00:31:39,070
え？
Huh?

426
00:31:39,070 --> 00:31:40,070
ちょっと...
Wait...

427
00:31:40,070 --> 00:31:43,070
あ、あ、ごめんごめん、やっぱりじゃあね、やっぱり撮りたいみたいだから。
Ah, sorry, sorry. It seems he really wants to take a photo.

428
00:31:43,070 --> 00:31:44,870
あ、やっぱりね。
Ah, I knew it.

429
00:31:44,870 --> 00:31:46,570
コロネすきいたもんね。
There's a Koronesuki there.

430
00:31:46,570 --> 00:31:48,070
撮りますか。
Shall we take one?

431
00:31:48,070 --> 00:31:49,870
コロネすき、ころさん好き？
Koronesuki, do you like Koro-san?

432
00:31:49,870 --> 00:31:52,570
好き？ころさん好き？
Do you like her? Do you like Koro-san?

433
00:31:53,070 --> 00:31:55,270
あ、よかった。え、マリンも好き？
Ah, thank goodness. Do you like Marine too?

434
00:31:55,270 --> 00:31:56,870
間に入ろう。
Let me get in between.

435
00:31:56,870 --> 00:31:57,870
なんでだよ！
Why?!

436
00:31:57,870 --> 00:32:00,870
コロネすきなのにころさんの隣に立てない気分どう？
How does it feel to be a Koronesuki but unable to stand next to Koro-san?

437
00:32:00,870 --> 00:32:03,470
嬉しい？マリンが隣で。
Are you happy Marine is next to you?

438
00:32:04,070 --> 00:32:05,170
嬉しくない...
Not happy...

439
00:32:05,170 --> 00:32:06,670
本当は好きなの。
He actually likes her.

440
00:32:06,670 --> 00:32:08,570
やめろ、やめろよ！
Stop it, stop it!

441
00:32:08,570 --> 00:32:10,570
ダメ、もうダメ。帰るよ、もう。
No, that's enough. I'm going back.

442
00:32:10,570 --> 00:32:11,570
はい、帰ろう。
Okay, let's go back.

443
00:32:11,570 --> 00:32:13,570
はい、今日はね、今日のバンドメンバーがいましたけれど。ですね。
Yes, today we had our band members here.

444
00:32:13,570 --> 00:32:14,270
ええ。
Yes.

445
00:32:14,270 --> 00:32:15,570
はい、え、マリンとも最後撮りたい？
Okay, do you want to take a photo with Marine at the end?

446
00:32:15,570 --> 00:32:16,870
あ、撮ろう撮ろう撮ろう。
Ah, let's take one!

447
00:32:16,870 --> 00:32:19,470
せっかくね。フォーエバーヤングだから、今日は。
Might as well. Since we are Forever Young today.

448
00:32:19,470 --> 00:32:21,070
マイク、マリン...
The mic, Marine...

449
00:32:21,070 --> 00:32:24,070
マイク、間違えちゃってるけどさ。
You got the mic wrong.

450
00:32:24,070 --> 00:32:26,570
マイクね。うん、いいよいいよ。
Oh, the mic. Yeah, that's fine.

451
00:32:26,570 --> 00:32:29,570
でかい声で喋ると拾うから。
Speak louder so it picks up.

452
00:32:29,570 --> 00:32:30,570
でかい声で...
Speak louder...

453
00:32:30,570 --> 00:32:31,570
撮れた？
Did we get it?

454
00:32:31,570 --> 00:32:32,870
いけてる？
Is it working?

455
00:32:32,870 --> 00:32:34,070
太犬？
Futoinu?

456
00:32:34,070 --> 00:32:36,070
中心として写って...
It's captured as the center...

457
00:32:36,070 --> 00:32:38,270
え、かわいく撮れたね。
Ah, we got a cute photo.

458
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:39,270
うん。ありがとう、マリン。
Yeah. Thank you, Marine.

459
00:32:39,270 --> 00:32:40,270
ありがとう。
Thank you.

460
00:32:40,270 --> 00:32:42,570
で、ちょっと次の曲があるから行くけど。次の曲。
Well, I have to go because the next song is starting.

461
00:32:42,570 --> 00:32:43,470
うん、次の曲。
Yeah, the next song.

462
00:32:43,470 --> 00:32:44,270
1人で帰れる？
Can you go back alone?

463
00:32:44,270 --> 00:32:46,470
おお、ええ、そう...うん、大丈夫。
Oh, uh, yeah, I'm fine.

464
00:32:46,470 --> 00:32:48,070
じゃあ、バンドメンバーのことよろしく。
Well then, take care of the band members.

465
00:32:48,070 --> 00:32:49,070
え？
Huh?

466
00:32:49,070 --> 00:32:50,070
じゃあ、マリン、バイバイ。
Well then, bye-bye, Marine.

467
00:32:50,070 --> 00:32:52,070
よろしくって何よ？よろしく。
"Take care" of what? Take care...

468
00:32:52,070 --> 00:32:54,870
え、どんなムードなの、これ？あ、え？
Huh? What kind of mood is this? Ah, eh?

469
00:32:54,870 --> 00:32:59,070
あ、みんな、あ、え、どうして？みんな、次の曲だよ。
Ah, everyone, eh, why? Everyone, next song!

470
00:33:02,070 --> 00:33:05,070
ラララ...
Lalala...

471
00:33:07,570 --> 00:33:08,570
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

472
00:33:08,570 --> 00:33:10,870
サボり方とか 甘え方とか
How to slack off, how to baby myself...

473
00:33:10,870 --> 00:33:13,270
逃げ方とか言い訳の仕方とか
How to run away, how to make excuses...

474
00:33:13,270 --> 00:33:15,870
やっと覚えてきた 身につけてきた
I finally learned them, I acquired them,

475
00:33:15,870 --> 00:33:18,570
柔らかい頭
my flexible mind.

476
00:33:18,570 --> 00:33:20,970
カッコのつけ方 調子のこき方
How to act cool, how to get ahead of myself...

477
00:33:20,970 --> 00:33:23,470
腹の据え方 良い年のこき方
How to steel my resolve, how to grow old gracefully...

478
00:33:23,470 --> 00:33:25,870
脂のりに乗った 濁った目をした
Full of fat, with muddy eyes...

479
00:33:25,870 --> 00:33:29,570
だらしない身体
this sloppy body.

480
00:33:30,070 --> 00:33:32,470
嫌われ方や 宥められ方や
How to be disliked, how to be pacified...

481
00:33:32,470 --> 00:33:35,470
アットマーク 叱られ方とか 綺麗なぶつかり方
How to be scolded, and how to clash gracefully.

482
00:33:35,470 --> 00:33:38,270
もっと覚えたいことが山のようにある
There are mountains of things I still want to learn.

483
00:33:38,270 --> 00:33:41,070
のびしろしかないわ
I've got nothing but room to grow!

484
00:33:41,070 --> 00:33:43,070
わっわっわ のびしろしかないわ
Woah, woah, woah, nothing but room to grow!

485
00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:45,870
わっわっわ のびしろしかないわ
Woah, woah, woah, nothing but room to grow!

486
00:33:45,870 --> 00:33:47,870
のびしろしかないわ
Nothing but room to grow!

487
00:33:47,870 --> 00:33:52,070
俺らまだのびしろしかないわ
We've still got nothing but room to grow!

488
00:33:52,070 --> 00:33:55,070
悪者扱いされてきた街で
In the town where I was treated like a bad guy,

489
00:33:55,070 --> 00:33:57,870
悪者扱いされてきた大人へ
to the adult who was treated like a bad guy...

490
00:33:57,870 --> 00:34:00,070
変わりゆく俺 鏡の中へ
Transforming myself into the mirror...

491
00:34:00,070 --> 00:34:03,070
yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah

492
00:34:03,070 --> 00:34:05,670
去る者は追わない 弾くとこ弾いて
I won't chase those who leave, I play where I should...

493
00:34:05,670 --> 00:34:08,070
丸く収めた 軽くあしらって
Settling things smoothly, brushing them off lightly...

494
00:34:08,070 --> 00:34:10,570
鏡の中で笑ってるお前
You, smiling in the mirror...

495
00:34:10,570 --> 00:34:13,570
覆う気合を誓ったたったの三文字で
Swearing my motivation with just three characters.

496
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:16,870
日々重くなる足取りで
With steps growing heavier day by day,

497
00:34:16,870 --> 00:34:19,870
自分の歩幅で完走してる
I'm finishing the race at my own pace.

498
00:34:19,870 --> 00:34:22,070
かますとこかます 任すとこ任す
Pulling off what I must, leaving what I must...

499
00:34:22,070 --> 00:34:24,870
割と適当な段取りで
With relatively sloppy planning.

500
00:34:24,870 --> 00:34:27,470
やっと分かってきたかも
I think I might finally be figuring out...

501
00:34:27,470 --> 00:34:30,070
このポンコツの操縦の仕方
how to navigate this piece of junk.

502
00:34:30,070 --> 00:34:32,870
19の時のついに来たかより
Better than the 'it finally came' feeling at 19,

503
00:34:32,870 --> 00:34:35,470
もっと清々しい気持ち
a much more refreshing feeling.

504
00:34:35,470 --> 00:34:37,470
隅田川にかかる
Spanning the Sumida River...

505
00:34:37,470 --> 00:34:40,070
